  </page>

  <page xml:id="examples">
    <title>Examples of Linear Combinations and Span</title>
    
    <example workspace="2in">
      <statement>
        <p>
          Let <m>\vec u=\begin{bmatrix} -1\\ 4\\ 2\end{bmatrix}</m> and <m>\vec v=\begin{bmatrix} 5\\ 0\\ -3\end{bmatrix}</m>. Determine three vectors which are linear combinations of <m>\vec u</m> and <m>\vec v</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
            The following are linear combinations <m>\vec u</m> and <m>\vec v</m>.
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>3\vec u + 5\vec v = \begin{bmatrix} -3 \\ 12 \\ 6 \end{bmatrix} + \begin{bmatrix} 25 \\ 0 \\ -15 \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} 22 \\ 12 \\ -9 \end{bmatrix}</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>0\vec u + (-3)\vec v = \begin{bmatrix} -15 \\ 0 \\ 9 \end{bmatrix}</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>0\vec u + 0\vec v = \begin{bmatrix} 0 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{bmatrix} = \vec 0</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
            So, we have that <m>\begin{bmatrix} 22 \\ 12 \\ -9 \end{bmatrix}, \begin{bmatrix} -15 \\ 0 \\ 9 \end{bmatrix}, \vec 0 \in \textrm{Span}\left\{\vec u, \vec v\right\}</m>
        </p>
    </solution>
    </example>
    

    <example workspace="2in" xml:id="ex-span">
      <statement>
        <p>
          Let <m>\vec u=\begin{bmatrix} -1\\ 4\\ 2\end{bmatrix}</m> and <m>\vec v=\begin{bmatrix} 5\\ 0\\ -3\end{bmatrix}</m>. Determine if <m>\vec w = \begin{bmatrix} 2 \\ 12 \\ 3 \end{bmatrix}</m> is in <m>\textrm{Span}(\vec u, \vec v)</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
            Note that <m>\vec w \in\textrm{Span}\{\vec u, \vec v\}</m> if and only if <m>\vec w</m> can be written as a linear combination of the vectors <m>\vec u</m> and <m>\vec v</m>; that is, if and only if there exist <m>c_1, c_2 \in \mathbb{R}</m> so that <me>c_1\vec u + c_2 \vec v = \vec w \iff \begin{bmatrix}-c_1 + 5c_2 \\ 4c_1 \\ 2c_1 - 3c_2 \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} 2 \\ 12 \\ 3 \end{bmatrix}</me> Note that this leads to the following system of linear equations: <md>
                \left\{\begin{array}{rrrrr}
                -c_1 \amp + \amp 5c_2 \amp = \amp 2 \\ 4c_1 \amp \amp \amp = \amp 12 \\ 2c_1 \amp - \amp 3c_2 \amp = \amp 3 \end{array}\right.
            </md>
            We will determine if this system has a solution by row reducing the corresponding augmented matrix. Note that
            <md>
                \begin{bmatrix} -1 \amp 5 \amp \rvert \amp 2 \\ 4 \amp 0 \amp \rvert \amp 12 \\ 2 \amp -3 \amp \rvert \amp 3 \end{bmatrix} \sim \begin{bmatrix}1 \amp -5 \amp \rvert \amp -2 \\ 0 \amp 20 \amp \rvert \amp 20 \\ 0 \amp 7 \amp \rvert \amp 7 \end{bmatrix} \sim \begin{bmatrix} 1 \amp 0 \amp \rvert \amp 3 \\ 0 \amp 1 \amp \rvert \amp 1 \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp \rvert \amp 0 \end{bmatrix}
            </md>
            It follows that the system has the solution <m>c_1 = 3</m> and <m>c_2 = 1</m>. Therefore, we have that <md>
                \vec w = 3\vec u + 1\vec v \in \textrm{Span}\{\vec u, \vec v\}
            </md>            
        </p>
    </solution>
    </example>
    
  </page>

  <page xml:id="example-span">
    <title>Example: Membership in a Span</title>
  <p>
      In general, any two non-parallel vectors in <m>\mathbb{R}^3</m> span a plane through the origin. 
      Every vector in that plane is a linear combination of the two.
    </p>

    <figure xml:id="fig-plane-span">
      <caption>Two nonparallel vectors in <m>\mathbb{R}^3</m> span a plane through the origin.</caption>
      <image xml:id="img-plane-span" width="30%">
        <description>
        A translucent plane through the origin with two nonparallel vectors drawn from the origin; 
        coordinate axes are shown for reference.
      </description>
        <latex-image>
          <preamble>
          </preamble>
          <tex>
\tdplotsetmaincoords{74}{100}
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=2.4,
  axis/.style={-{Stealth[length=4pt]},black},
  vectorC/.style={-{Stealth[length=4pt]},black,very thick},
  vectorV/.style={-{Stealth[length=4pt]},blue,very thick},
  tdplot_main_coords
]
  \coordinate (O) at (0,0,0);
  \coordinate (X) at (2,0,0);
  \coordinate (Y) at (0,1,0);
  \coordinate (Z) at (0,0,1);
  \coordinate (X1) at (1,1,0);
  \coordinate (X2) at (1,0,1);
  \coordinate (X3) at (2,1,1);

  % plane spanned by X1 and X2
